{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC14"]]},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"With Student Accounts and Family Sharing, kids under age 13 can now have fully-featured accounts for buying apps and In-App Purchases. However, regulations in the US and other countries limit what information you can collect from kids without parental permission. Learn about the new account programs, whether and how to check the age of your app’s user, what you can and can’t do without parental permission, and how to request parental consent if you need to."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"kind":"article","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC14-717-Kids-and-Apps","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc14-717-kids-and-apps"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"role":"sampleCode","title":"Kids and Apps","roleHeading":"WWDC14","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2014\/717\/","type":"reference"}},"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC14":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc14","abstract":[{"text":"Xcode 6, Swift 1.0, iOS 8, macOS 10.10 (Yosemite).","type":"text